The paper deals with the optimization of transmission rates and power allocation in wireless networks, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of non-orthogonal multiple access (NOMA) is a key aspect of the paper, which is a technique commonly used in wireless communication systems (cs.SY). The paper also analyzes the performance of different access methods, which is a topic in multimedia systems (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG).
